<number id="701024FF221CE755FBC52023C4CE1634" box="[1133,1197,1842,1868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C66736D8221CE754FF6D2046C1981184" blockId="2.[151,1437,1842,2017]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,252]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Differs from congeners in short length of truncate vertex (
<figureCitation id="5EE32A5D221CE755FCDC2046C3DE1609" box="[884,957,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,272,1484,1508]" captionTargetBox="[277,1298,860,1423]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,845,1460]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6 (after Medler 1992). Figs. 1 – 4, A. decepta; Figs. 5 – 6, A. abrupta; 1, frons; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, sutural margin; 4, male genitalia, left lateral view; 5, frons; 6, head, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276348/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="701024FF221CE755FC042046C3DE1609" box="[940,957,1879,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); frons truncate dorsally, margin formed by broad U-shaped carina which medially terminates longitudinal frontal carina (
<figureCitation id="5EE32A5D221CE755FBCE206DC4D316EE" box="[1126,1200,1916,1942]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,272,1484,1508]" captionTargetBox="[277,1298,860,1423]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,845,1460]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6 (after Medler 1992). Figs. 1 – 4, A. decepta; Figs. 5 – 6, A. abrupta; 1, frons; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, sutural margin; 4, male genitalia, left lateral view; 5, frons; 6, head, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276348/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="701024FF221CE755FB37206DC4D316EE" box="[1183,1200,1916,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Postclaval sutural margin extended at angle of 
<number id="701024FF221CE755FE4120B3C27416C4" box="[489,535,1954,1980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="165.0">165</number>
° from claval apex, meeting apical margin at angle of 
<number id="701024FF221CE755FB3C20B3C4D516C4" box="[1172,1206,1954,1980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="65.0">65</number>
°; numerous closely spaced terminal veins in submarginal area; submarginal area 
<quantity id="01209B3D221CE755FCCD20D6C3A31699" box="[869,960,1991,2017]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
wide. Tegmen ochreous, color obscured by dusting of white waxy powder, veins dull green, margin narrowly red, without black spots or lines. 
<typeStatus id="1963887A221DE754FF3F27ACC16711AF" box="[151,260,189,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Holotype</typeStatus>
valvulae III with row of heavy spines on ventral margin, same as seen in 
<taxonomicName id="01D84D5B221DE754FBCC27ACC4BC11AE" box="[1124,1247,189,214]" class="Insecta" family="Flatidae" genus="Amasha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decepta">
<emphasis id="F4ACEACA221DE754FBCC27ACC4BC11AE" box="[1124,1247,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">A. decepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="F4ACEACA221DE754FF6D27F3C10B1184" bold="true" box="[197,360,226,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="BECF7648221DE754FEC727F3C1941184" box="[367,503,226,252]" name="Philippines" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
